<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06078089 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06078089 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Diagram; DIAGRAM: Knight-Ridder Tribune News; Sports Facts; NCAA tournamentrecords  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  SPORT; QA  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Q What does the plus-minus rating in hockey mean and how is it calculated?;   A The plus-minus rating is used to determine whether a player is on the icewhen more goals are scored by his team or the opposition.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  (NOT SO) DUMB QUESTIONS  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     A player receives a plus every time he is on the ice when his team scoresan even-strength or short-handed goal, and is charged with a minus every timehe is on the ice when the opposition scores an even-strength or short-handedgoal. A player is not credited with a plus if he is on the ice when his teamscores a power-play goal, and is not charged with a minus if he is on the icewhen the opposition scores on a power play.;    In theory, players with poorplus-minus ratings are weaker defensively than players with higher ratings.;   Since the 1982-83 season, the NHL has presented an annual award to the playerwith the best plus-minus rating at the end of the season (to be eligible aplayer must appear in at least 60 games). Defenseman Paul Cavalini of the St.Louis Blues won the award last season with a rating of andplus;38.  </TEXT><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910318  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  March  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  DIAGRAM  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  216  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday March 18, 199100078089,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>